<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Plane Engine,0118</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Jetliner Engine Fails</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USAir and federal officials are investigating
the failure of an engine from a Boeing 737 jetliner en route from
Pittsburgh to Newark, N.J., according to the airline.
   USAir Flight 264 returned to Greater Pittsburgh International
Airport Monday morning after the jetliner's right engine compressor
stalled and oil pressure dropped about 45 miles east of Pittsburgh,
said USAir spokesman David Shipley.
   None of the 80 passengers and crew members aboard were injured,
he said.
   The aircraft was taken out of service and was being checked by
USAir and Federal Aviation Administration officials, Shipley said.
   The passengers and their luggage went to Newark aboard another
USAir jetliner.
</TEXT>
