<HEAD>London Share Prices Slightly Firmer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices opened slightly firmer in London
today as traders reacted to news of a possible settlement of the
strike at Ford Motor Co.'s British plants and to a rise on Wall
Street.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index opened up 3.1
points at 1,737.7 and by 9:45 a.m. it was up 6.9 points at 1,741.5,
or 0.39 percent.
   Traders said 36 of the index's shares were showing gains in
quiet trading, 20 were showing losses and the rest were unchanged.
   The Ford strike had worried the market as traders feared it
heralded a round of higher private-sector pay claims in Britain. A
settlement reached by negotiators will be voted on Thursday by
striking workers.
   In New York on Tuesday, the Dow Jones industrial average
advanced 22.71 points, or 1.15 percent, to 2,005.97.
