<TEXT>
   The U.S.-led United Nations Command
said Wednesday it has proposed that a Korean Military Armistice
Commission meeting be held at the truce village of Panmunjom on
Feb. 23.
   Command officials said the move was in response to a North
Korean proposal that sought to convene the meeting Feb. 15.
   If held, it would be the 441st meeting since the Korean
armistice agreement was signed in 1953.
