<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--HHS Appointment,130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Assistant Secretary Named in Health Department</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ralph R. Reed, a physician from Lawrence,
Kan., has been appointed deputy assistant secretary for health of
the Department of Health and Human Services.
   He becomes the top aide to Dr. Robert E. Windom, the No. 2
official at HHS, in helping oversee the Public Health Service.
   The service consists of seven agencies, including the Food and
Drug Administration, the National Institutes of Health and the
Centers for Disease Control.
   In announcing the appointment this month, HHS Secretary Otis R.
Bowen said Reed also will play a role in providing medical and
health policy guidance to other department components, especially
the agency that administers the Medicare and Medicaid programs.
   Reed replaces Lowell T. Harmison who recently resigned as acting
deputy assistant secretary for health.
