2,005.97, closing above 2,000 for the first time since it stood at
2,051.89 on Jan. 7.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declines by more than 4 to 3 on the
NYSE. Big Board volume totaled 135.38 million shares Tuesday,
against 144.86 million in last Friday's session.
